                <h2>Employment</h2>
                <div class="resumeblock">
                    <h3><a href="http://www.lavieencode.net">"La Vie en Code" Blog </a><span>2015 - present</span></h3>
                    <h4>Founder/Writer</h4>
                    <p>Creating content aimed toward women and individuals interested in a self-educated path to a career in web development. Launched successful affiliate campaigns with Udemy and Treehouse, quickly attracting invitations for large-scale targeted promotions and advertising. La Vie en Code hosts more than 500 views per week, with prominent social media hubs on Facebook and Twitter.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="resumeblock">
                    <h3><a href="http://www.shopkeep.com">ShopKeep </a><span>2014 - 2015</span></h3>
                    <h4>Customer Care Manager</h4>
                    <p>Promoted as Portland&rsquo;s second Customer Care Manager after just 5 months. Built and led a team of up to 12 Customer Care Advisors through Q1 of 2015, budget restrictions and consistent understaffing. Consistently recognized for exemplary skills in communication, teamwork and project management.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="resumeblock">
                    <h3><a href="http://www.shopkeep.com">ShopKeep </a><span>2014</span></h3>
                    <h4>Customer Care Advisor</h4>
                    <p>Supported ShopKeep&rsquo;s 13,000+ subscriber base in the new Portland, OR office as one of the first 3 Portland-based Customer Care Advisors. Strong demonstrated skills in cloud-based and iPad app/POS hardware troubleshooting, customer issue de-escalation, and creative and resourceful problem-solving.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="resumeblock">
                    <h3>Merchants Exchange of Portland <span>2012 - 2014</span></h3>
                    <h4>Association Administrator</h4>
                    <p>Worked with Board of Directors of 7 not-for-profit associations serviced by (and including) Merchants Exchange and its Executive Director to streamline processes based on individual association needs. Launched and managed successful email marketing campaigns for association events, and designed print marketing materials/annual reports for associations. Successfully increased overall association membership by more than 10% in less than 2 years.</p>
                </div>

