    <!-- section BLOG -->
    <section id="sectionBlog">
    	<div class="container">

        <!-- section TITLE -->
    		<div class="sectionTitle">
    			<h1>"La Vie en Code" Blog</h1>
    			<h4>Dedicated to the Self-Educated</h4>
        		<div class="separatorlineblack"></div>
        <!-- END section TITLE -->
    		</div>
            <p>La Vie en Code is my pride and joy. Since embarking on this ridiculous endeavor to transition into web development fully back in May 2015, I had wanted to write about my experiences. I feel strongly that women--and particularly, minority women--are often afraid to take the initial steps toward web dev, despite the fact that they may be extremely interested, or even have some skills under their belt already.</p>

            <p>I am out to eliminate this fear.</p>

            <p>When is the last time you saw code anthropomorphized as a speed dating partner? How about a genuine story of a woman's first hackathon? You'll find it here: the self-deprecation over my own code being weird, the resulting pick-me-up talk to myself about not comparing myself to other developers... the laughter, and the tears.</p>

            <p>Are you ready to come read now?</p>

            <a class="btn btn-default btn-lg noteasing" href="http://www.lavieencode.net" role="button">Visit My Blog</a>
    	</div>
    </section>
